				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Polycrystalline silicon, also known as polysilicon or mc-Si, is a high purity, polycrystalline form of silicon used as a raw material by the solar photovoltaic and electronics industry. It is produced from metallurgical grade silicon by a chemical purification process, called the Siemens process. It has an impurity level of 1 part per billion or less. It is used in solar panels and electronic devices, offering benefits like lower cost and environmental friendliness, but has drawbacks such as lower efficiency, space requirements, and a shorter lifespan.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">多晶硅，也被称为多晶硅或mc-Si，是一种高纯度的多晶硅，被太阳能光伏和电子工业用作原料。它是通过一种称为西门子过程的化学纯化过程，从冶金级硅中生产出来的。它的杂质水平为十亿分之一或更少。它被用于太阳能板和电子设备，提供了诸如较低成本和环保等优点，但也有诸如效率较低、空间需求大和寿命较短等缺点。</common:generalComment>
